Titolo: 3 Skulls of the Toltecs

Anno: 1996

Descrizione: 3 Skulls of the Toltecs is a point-and-click graphic adventure game designed by Revistronic for IBM PC compatibles published by Warner Interactive Europe in 1996. The game features 3rd-person perspective, inventory-based puzzle solving, and side-scrolling cartoon graphics. 3 Skulls of the Toltecs sold of 25,000 copies in Spain and 200,000 across Europe. Revistronic followed the game with two sequels: The Westerner (2003) and Fenimore Fillmore's Revenge (2008).

